### File Structure
```
RealEstate/
│
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
├── README.md
│
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── property_search.html
│   ├── property_details.html
│   ├── property_inquiry.html
│   ├── my_inquiries.html
│   ├── my_favorites.html
│   ├── agents.html
│   └── locations.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (property and agent images if any)
│
└── data/
    ├── properties.txt
    ├── locations.txt
    ├── inquiries.txt
    ├── favorites.txt
    └── agents.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python application file that handles routing, data processing, and business logic for all eight pages. It reads from and writes to the local text files in the 'data' directory. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic is consolidated here.

- requirements.txt
  Lists Python dependencies required to run the application (e.g., Flask or other web frameworks).

- README.md
  Documentation file describing the project setup, running instructions, and overview.

- templates/
  Contains all HTML template files for the web pages, each corresponding to one of the eight pages defined in the requirements:
    - dashboard.html: Dashboard page layout and elements.
    - property_search.html: Property search page with filters and property grid.
    - property_details.html: Detailed view of a selected property.
    - property_inquiry.html: Form for submitting property inquiries.
    - my_inquiries.html: Displays user inquiries and their statuses.
    - my_favorites.html: Lists favorite properties with management options.
    - agents.html: Directory of real estate agents.
    - locations.html: Featured locations with sorting and navigation.

- static/
  Contains static assets used by the web pages:
    - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
    - js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering).
    - images/: Folder for property and agent images if applicable.

- data/
  Stores all application data in text files as specified:
    - properties.txt: Property listings data.
    - locations.txt: Location information.
    - inquiries.txt: Property inquiries submitted by users.
    - favorites.txt: User favorite properties.
    - agents.txt: Real estate agents data.
```
